purchase. Which is ironic. Last time I went on this trip, in 2024, I made my first rent payment for the townhouse...and I could barely do that then. Two years later, feeling as if I am in the same boat. \n\nRelief, a windfall, progress, margin, something. I need something. \n\nI have a solid lineup of projects though, and if they dont' create income now I think they will in the future. Cost to maintain is minimal, I think. Time will tell as I continue using things and especially when I open things up to other users. \n\nI've got the three mac apps that I am testing and using daily at this point. Those require an apple developer license ($99/year) in order to get them into the mac app store. Not doing that yet, but there's potential there for income. The calendar app will be free (support via Plink, maybe), the gateway to the two paid apps: TidyBar ($9.99) and TidyStage ($14.99) or the bundle for $19.99. Potential for income. That's a long road though, I know that. But it is a doorway. \n\nThen several web apps, I've gone through all of this before but doing so again is how I process: \n\n1. The Slot - this one will remain free and is the gateway into...\n2. Endpaper - place to think and write and publish to/from\n3. Cadence - place to write a drip newsletter, maybe with support for having a paid publication\n\nThat feels right. Three on each, one free as the doorway, then two paid if they like what I have to offer. \n\nPlink is mine for now. FirstThing.Day and MadeMy.Day are two other small doorways, plink being used to receive anything if it has been a helpful thing for someone. \n\nThen I have a standalong e-book, _Splinched_. First chapter will be free. Then want to sell the bundle of eBook & Tools for $39. \n\nI expect none of it to actually generate any income. So if it does make anything then I'll be pleasantly surprised. \n\nOh, and also have BestCigarMatches.com - but that income is meant specifically for Lindsay and for her being able to eventually stop cleaning if she would like to. It has just become too much for her hands to do what is needed since the car accident. My hope is that BCM would give her the option to quit her job if she'd like to. \n\nSo. Usual stuff today. No stars to promote about of this writing time, and that's ok. \n\nTime to move into what is next. Finishing coffee and cracking open what I can of _Splinched_."
